# Microsoft OneNote Configuration (Microsoft Graph API)
# Create a Public Client Application (Mobile and desktop applications) in Azure Portal:
# https://portal.azure.com/ -> Microsoft Entra ID -> App registrations -> New registration
# Supported account types: "Accounts in any organizational directory (Any Microsoft Entra ID tenant - Multitenant) and personal Microsoft accounts (e.g. Skype, Xbox)"
# Under Authentication -> Add a platform -> Mobile and desktop applications -> check "https://login.microsoftonline.com/common/oauth2/nativeclient" and "msal[YOUR_CLIENT_ID]://auth"
# Enable "Allow public client flows" under Advanced Settings if needed.
ONENOTE_CLIENT_ID=your_microsoft_graph_client_id
ONENOTE_TENANT_ID=common
